The rich parvenu became common in Rome during the last years of the Republic. The increase of tbis class, chiefly made up of freed· men, was fostered by the disorders and confiscations of the civil wars; so that society was contaminated by those vulgar rich who wished to establisb themselves in it. They were not satisfied with enrollment in the equestrian order, but pressed even into the senate, which Octavian purged in the winter of 29-28B.c. Cf. Suet.
